From d617cdf0270f25dd534b28302e02c286dd9c5da4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 2025 10:01:35 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: PROTOCOL: wifi: ath12k: Support 6 GHz MLO with SP

Currently, the driver does not have the support for handling
power mode change commands for an MLD with two 6 GHz links,
where each link is in different 6 GHz power modes.

Also, for filling the set TPC WMI command, ath12k uses the
power_type field from the 'ieee80211_bss_conf' structure for
STA interface and the 'reg_6g_power_mode' from the wdev for
AP type intarface. But, this field in the wdev is removed and
moved to a links field of the wdev in the latest cfg80211.

To fix this,
   (1) Add new attribute link id to the power mode change command.
   (2) Use the link id sent by the application as part of the
       power mode change command to determine the link / radio
       for which the power mode change command is sent.
   (3) Also, pass the link id as part of the power mode changed
       event to the userspace to indicate which link has
       changed its power mode.
   (4) Use the power mode from the 'ieee80211_bss_conf' structure
       for both STA and AP interfaces. This works because, in
       the latest cfg80211, the power mode is updated in the
       'ieee80211_bss_conf' structure for both STA and AP
       interfaces.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
subsys/0048-cfg80211-mac80211-regulatory-awgn-and-6g-channel-cha.patch
subsys/0340-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-cfg80211-mac80211-Store-6-GHz-powe.patch

Signed-off-by: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
